Date: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2019
Author: GilroyCA
Title: Mini Box MAXI Capacity!
Body: I'm a 1-star or 5-star reviewer, I don't waste time with anything in the middle. It's either super awesome or so bad you want to know about it in order for me to write a review.Having said that, this is a 5-star purchase.  My overall expectations were pretty low as I was convinced this box was not going to do the job for me.However.I moved in to it and this is what's in my box right now:13 necklaces7 bracelets3 anklets1 watch26 rings54 pair of earrings9 charms/pendants/pinsYou should know there is a tiny room left for another ring or two, but basically this box is packed full but not in such a way that I'm having to dig through it for stuff, I can still easily get to what I need even though a couple of cubbies have more than one item in them.  I'm an OCD neat freak and must have easy access to things and they have to be organized. This box actually makes me happy just knowing everything is in one organized place (before I had earrings in a nightstand drawer, rings and necklaces in the safe, my watch and a couple bracelets were in my desk drawer, etc).There is one con and I need to mention it. The box is off-gassing and fumey probably from the glues.  I've been letting it air for the last few days and either I'm really used to the smell or it's actually much better than it was. I'm not concerned that this will be on-going, it's like new carpet, eventually it airs out.Two thumbs up and 5-star rating from a 51 year old broad in California. Cheers.I only gave this a 3star for giftable, and that's my opinion for what it's worth. I think a jewelry box is a very personal thing and I would never choose one for someone else.As for the locking mechanism, lots of folks said they wish you could lock the whole box, but really, if someone comes in your house, they're going to pick the whole thing up and walk out with it. The top compartment that locks is sufficient for prying fingers at home.

Date: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2020
Author: Alexis
Title: Beautiful but not “perfect”
Body: Five stars because it was meant for me.Some things you may want to be aware of though..This jewelry box is not in any way brand new. Maybe not ever purchased but this is not a new product. It has that smell of being from a garage sale or left in a basement. The interior is discolored and it almost made me rethink using it. Then I was like, this thing is beautiful. With the white leather look to the amount it holds. I feel if you have a massive collection, this may not be for you. It holds a lot but my collection is small in comparison to others. I decided it’s five stars because it’s meant for me, and I love it. I believe in that sort of thing. This beautiful jewelry box, unloved - not purchased. Finally has a home, haha.If you want sleek, shiny and brand new - this isn’t for you. If you want something beautiful on the outside and not perfect on the inside, hands down recommend. Do a good palo santo cleanse on it and you’re good to go. Perfect for me. I do not think it should be priced as high - that should be changed.

Date: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2021
Author: Star
Title: Lock is useless, but it’s way bigger than my old one and seems better quality (TLDR at bottom)
Body: I’ve had my original jewelry box since early 2015 and I’ve accumulated so much over the years it was so disorganized and overflowing. It wasn’t big enough to hang necklaces, so I used the sides to hang earrings and when I got this new one, had to get the enormous tangles out of all my chains. I wish I had a before picture from before I moved the jewelry to the new one; it was a mess. The first two photos are the old one.The new one is much bigger, and I’m able to hang my chains and necklaces. I read some reviews before I got it that you have to stuff the pendants in the bottom pockets and they tangle there, but I got around that by hanging them differently so they barely meet the little pocket at the bottom. Some of the areas are a little small; there were still some spots that I dedicated to chokers and these multicolored necklaces that are overflowing in the third drawer, but will probably tangle if I moved them to the big one, but I was able to fit my really long earrings there so that was nice. The little spots in the second drawer are amazing! i have so many pendants with no dedicated chains, so I switch them out a lot, and I had little areas where I could put them all, and where I could put my dangly earrings since there wasn’t a dedicated spot in the earring drawer (first drawer). I do love the earring drawer though, I can also put rings in it if I want. The dividers seem useless in the sense that I probably won’t put anything between them, since when you have to pull them out to take the earrings out anything there would all fall to the bottom. Under the bottom one is fine for small backings. If anyone knows a better way to use the earring drawer I’d love to know (for the dangly ones). I don’t wear watches but the top was great for all my bracelets once I took the watch pillows out; I kept one to use for the beaded stretchy bracelets just because it looks nice. I don’t have a lot of rings, so the top fit all mine, but I want more so I’ll probably have to move some to the earring drawer once I get more.The only thing I prefer about my old one (besides it came with a travel case you could take in and out, but I hardly used it, and it got stolen anyway) is that the lock actually mattered. All the sides closed around the drawers and buttons, then locked in place with the top, so you couldn’t get in without the key at all. This new one; the lock only locks the top. You can get to all the drawers and sides for necklaces without the key. This isn’t a huge deal for me, since I rarely locked my old box anyway, and it’s not like I have expensive jewelry. But it would be nice for if I was going out of town.TLDR,The lock only locks the top, so anything really valuable you’d have to put in there. The sides are great for keeping necklaces and chains untangled. In short, it’s a great box of you need space and love meticulous organization.

Title: Great jewelry box
Body: The reason I bought  this box was for my husband's watches. The rest of the box is for my earrings and necklaces. It looks more manly, but it certainly protects his watches.If you can get past the fact that it looks more for men, then you will love it like I do. It is very sturdy.

Date: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2023
Author: Artea R.
Title: Good material and plenty of storage
Body: The material on the outside is similar to leather and on the inside is a very softy one. Has plenty of storage space. The top compartment comes with a key if you have expensive jewelry. Each side has 8 hooks for necklaces. The rings space is kind of limited but plenty of space for earrings. The bottom drawer is the deeper one where you can keep sunglasses or hair claws. Overall love it.

Date: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2022
Author: Brhie
Title: Very functional. Absolutely love
Body: I don’t think I’ve bought something on Amazon that has made me this happy in a long time. This product is perfect. It’s very practical. I have a TON of jewelry and even after putting all of my jewelry in this thing I still have more space. All of the hardware feels sturdy and it doesn’t feel cheap. My also does not have a smell. I saw some reviews about a smell but mine does not. The only thing I would change about this is that the drawers didn’t pull all the way out. Other than that I absolutely love this product

Body: LOVE IT! It stores all my jewelry perfectly, and is the perfect size. I still have room left over even though I have plenty of jewelry. The only thing, is that it has that weird new plasticy smell (but doesn’t affect anything).
